state.name: IPESC Season 8 - GT3 Championship
state.rulesDescription:
Discord

You must sign up to our Discord server and be present in our race chat during the entire race.
Drivers are expected to listen to race briefings.

Points

In addition to the scoring system, IPESC awards +1 championship point for the fastest lap of the race per class.

Class selection

IPESC prides itself on being a welcoming community that is supportive of drivers of all experience levels.

  1. Use this site to see where your lap times sit in relation to our grids quali and race pace deltas.

  2. Self select the class most appropriate for your pace.

Qualifying


To promote equal qualifying opportunity, qualifying is split into two halves.
Admins will manage this during the race and expect ALL drivers to follow instructions.


First 10 minutes | AM class only
Last 10 minutes | PRO and SILVER classes only

Penalties

IPESC applies post race penalties.
View penalty time for each track here
Note: these are experimental and constantly being reviewed and revised for fairness and balance across a three class grid.

Repeat Offenders
On top of the base penalties, we track drivers penalty totals across a season.
Drivers will receive more significant penalties for multiple penalties across races.
Strikes will reset after receiving 5 strikes.
3 strikes = 1 x qualifying ban

Repeat offenders regulations
Defined as: Repeat offenders are drivers who receive a penalty two or more races in a season where penalties are monitored.

a) Repeat offenders will have their penalty increased from tier 1 to tier 2 for second offence then raised to tier 3 for the 3rd penalty, after the third penalty you will forfeit qualifying and start from the pits on the next race

Eg. 3 races with penalties over the season will result in a race start from the pits forfeiting qualifying position

a1) multiple penalties in one race does not constitute a repeat offender.

--

Penalties are going to be POST RACE time penalties only at this stage and will be enforced as below Incidents will be determined to be one of three criteria:

TIER 1
Offending car is solely responsible for a racing infringement leading to contact with another car which results in significant time loss to that car (this will be only obvious incidents ie we still want elbows out racing, also covers minor infringements when returning to track, etc)
Penalty = time penalty equivalent to a drive through penalty.
Drive through time penalties are based on each tracks pit lane entry to exit transition time this is individual for each track.

TIER 2
Offending car is solely responsible for a MAJOR racing infringement causing collisions to multiple cars as per tier 1 description. (this also will include careless race re-joins causing major damage to on track cars etc)
Penalty = Stop and go 30 seconds

TIER 3
Offending car is driving completely unsportsmanlike and purposefully in a way to cause damage or harm to another driverâ€™s race. (This is the very naughty one, and we doubt we will have any issues with this.)
Penalty = Stop and go 60 seconds

A stop and go penalty is the amount of time taken to enter the pits stop for 30/60 seconds and exit pit lane
